MISRA C++ 2008 Rule 3-2-3
A type, object or function that is used in multiple translation units shall be declared in one and only one file.

Explaination about "used in multiple translation units":
   - for type, every type shall be declared in one and only one file.
   - for object, every object with external linkage shall be declared in one and only one file.
   - for function, every function with external linkage shall be declared in one and only one file.

